==English==

===Etymology===
Russian [[копейка]] < Middle Russian [[копейка]] < [[копьё]], [[spear]] (from the image of a rider with a spear on the coins minted by Moscow after the capture of Novgorod in 1478).

===Noun===
'''kopek'''  (''plural:'' '''[[kopeks]]''')

# Russian monetary unit equals one-hundredth of a [[ruble]], also spelt [[copeck]], [[kopeck]].

===Usage note===
'''Kopek''' is the favored spelling used by [http://themoscowtimes.com the Moscow Times].

